        <caption>
          <p>The magnitudes of electrostatic binding forces between the detached capsomer and incomplete TCV capsid <bold>(A)</bold>, and the kinesin motor domain and microtubule <bold>(B)</bold>. In both panels, the strength of the binding forces is represented by the blue vertical histogram bars. The more negative value of binding force (KT/Ã), the stronger attractive electrostatic binding force. The changes of binding force as the separation distance increased were shown by the red moving average trendlines in both panels.</p>
